Output is `{"name":"Jane","age":30}` — exactly as expected. Here's the full program:

**Program.cs**
```csharp
using System.Text.Json;

var person = new Person("Jane", 30);

var options = new JsonSerializerOptions
{
    PropertyNamingPolicy = JsonNamingPolicy.CamelCase
};

Console.WriteLine(JsonSerializer.Serialize(person, options));

public record Person(string Name, int Age);
```

The key is `JsonNamingPolicy.CamelCase` — set it on `JsonSerializerOptions.PropertyNamingPolicy` and pass the options to `Serialize`. No extra packages needed; `System.Text.Json` is built into .NET 8.
